Assignment name  : snake_to_camel
Expected files   : snake_to_camel.c
Allowed functions: write
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write a program that takes a string in snake_case format and converts it to
lowerCamelCase.

The program must remove all underscores `_`.

If a lowercase letter comes after an underscore, it must be converted to
uppercase.

All other uppercase letters must be converted to lowercase.

The result must be followed by a newline.

If the number of parameters is not 1, the program displays only a newline.

Examples:

$> ./snake_to_camel "hello_world" | cat -e
helloWorld$
$> ./snake_to_camel "make_this_work" | cat -e
makeThisWork$
$> ./snake_to_camel "FOO_bar" | cat -e
fooBar$
$> ./snake_to_camel "alreadyCamel" | cat -e
alreadycamel$
$> ./snake_to_camel | cat -e
$
